0w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*_vaSqr_TE3MSJSCcKHW5uA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*_vaSqr_TE3MSJSCcKHW5uA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*_vaSqr_TE3MSJSCcKHW5uA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:552/1*_vaSqr_TE3MSJSCcKHW5uA.png 552w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:276/1*_vaSqr_TE3MSJSCcKHW5uA.png"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7"><strong>Backpropagation through time in LSTMs</strong></h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">As in the RNN model, our LSTM network outputs a prediction vector h(k) on the k-th time step. The knowledge encoded in the state vectors c(t) captures long-term dependencies and relations in the sequential data.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The length of the data sequences can be hundreds and even thousands of time steps, making it extremely difficult to learn using a basic RNN.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We compute the gradient used to update the network parameters, the computation is done over T time steps.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
